I’m looking to get a head start in programming next year’s MAXSwerve or our team. I realized that the MAXSwerve Java Template uses the “ADIS16470” gyroscope. I tried to look at our team code from last year as the setup was the same but when I tried to copy the gyroscope initialization, I was getting errors. I imported all the necessary packages and vendor reps (I think) and it’s not working like it’s supposed to. This is the current state of the code:

Screenshot 2024-12-30 2155441920×1140 251 KB

Screenshot 2024-12-30 2156051920×1140 238 KB

I also tried to use the constructor like this: m_gyro = new AHRS(comType: null);
But I was getting Fatal Errors and no code getting deployed to the robot with this constructor. We use a NavX2-MXP connected to the RoboRIO via the MXP port on the RIO.

Something I should warn you about is that some of the older NavX’s had a problem where their yaw wasn’t properly calibrated, and would result in a 20 degree drift after a few rotations.
My team also ran into this issue, but we were unable to fix it (there are instructions on how to fix it online, might just be user error on our part). Maybe rotate your drivebase a few times and make sure that this isn’t an issue before you commit to the navx.
